    },
)
```
It is recommended to use an SSD instead of an HDD when using object spilling for memory-intensive workloads. If you are using an HDD, it is recommended to specify a large buffer size (> 1MB) to reduce IO requests during spilling.

Ensure that you have enough disk space in the spill directory to avoid running out of disk space and causing `OutOfDiskError` exceptions. You can adjust the threshold for local object spilling by setting the `local_fs_capacity_threshold` parameter in the `object_spilling_config`. The default threshold is 0.95 (95%). You can disable the protection by setting it to 1.

